---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Container from "../components/Container.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Starter terms of service for a small 3D print-on-demand service website."
  pathname="/terms-of-service/"
>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of Service"
    description="Starter terms for a small custom 3D printing business. This page should be reviewed and tailored to the actual business, jurisdiction, warranty position, and order workflow before launch."
  />

  <section class="section-shell">
    <Container>
      <article class="legal-copy max-w-4xl">
        <section>
          <p>Effective date: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>
            These Terms of Service govern the use of this website and any custom 3D printing
            services provided by <strong>[Insert legal business name]</strong>. By using the site,
            submitting a quote request, or placing an order, you agree to these terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Services</h2>
          <p>
            The business provides custom 3D printing services for prototypes, replacement parts,
            hobby projects, small-batch parts, and related custom jobs, subject to equipment limits,
            material availability, and job suitability.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Quotes And Orders</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>All pricing is provided by quote unless otherwise stated in writing.</li>
            <li>Quotes may depend on file review, material selection, quantity, finish, and delivery requirements.</li>
            <li>A quote does not become a binding order until the business confirms acceptance and any required payment terms are met.</li>
            <li>Quoted lead times are estimates unless explicitly guaranteed in writing.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Customer Files And Responsibilities</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>The customer is responsible for confirming that uploaded files, measurements, and project requirements are accurate.</li>
            <li>The customer is responsible for ensuring they have the right to submit any model, drawing, logo, or design for printing.</li>
            <li>The business may refuse jobs that appear unsafe, infringing, unlawful, or technically unsuitable.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Print Variance And Expectations</h2>
          <p>
            3D printing is a manufacturing process with practical tolerances and visible process
            characteristics. Layer lines, support marks, minor surface variation, and reasonable
            dimensional variance may occur depending on geometry, material, and finish level.
          </p>
          <p>
            Customers should identify any critical dimensions, load requirements, or appearance
            requirements before production begins.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Material And Use Limitations</h2>
          <p>
            Printed parts may not be suitable for every use. Unless specifically agreed in writing,
            printed parts are not certified for medical, aerospace, life-safety, or other
            high-liability applications.
          </p>
          <p>
            Placeholder for legal review: <strong>[Insert any additional prohibited or restricted use language]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Payment</h2>
          <p>
            Payment terms, deposit requirements, and accepted payment methods should be stated here.
            If partial payment, prepayment, or custom invoicing is required, that should be made
            explicit before launch.
          </p>
          <p>
            Placeholder for legal review: <strong>[Insert payment terms, taxes, and late-payment language]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Cancellations, Changes, And Reprints</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Orders may not be cancellable once printing or material preparation has begun.</li>
            <li>Design changes after quote approval may require a revised quote and schedule.</li>
            <li>Any reprint or refund policy should be clearly defined here, including how fit or quality claims are reviewed.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Placeholder for legal review: <strong>[Insert final cancellation, refund, and reprint terms]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Shipping And Pickup</h2>
          <p>
            Delivery dates are estimates unless specifically guaranteed. Risk of loss and ownership
            transfer terms should be clarified here, especially for shipped orders versus local
            pickup.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            Customers retain ownership of their submitted designs except to the extent required for
            the business to review, quote, print, package, and deliver the order. The business
            retains ownership of its website content, branding, and internal manufacturing methods.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Limitation Of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent allowed by law, the business should limit liability for indirect,
            incidental, special, and consequential damages. Liability caps and disclaimers should be
            reviewed by counsel before launch.
          </p>
          <p>
            Placeholder for legal review: <strong>[Insert final limitation of liability and disclaimer language]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These terms should specify the governing law and venue:
            <strong> [Insert state or jurisdiction]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Changes To These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            The business may update these Terms of Service from time to time. Updated terms should
            be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms of Service should be directed to:
            <strong> [Insert legal business contact details]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
